-- Base Metals Gain as Finance Ministers Said to Reach Deal on Greek Bailout
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-02-21T03:21:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-21/base-metals-gain-as-finance-ministers-said-to-reach-deal-on-greek-bailout.html
Copper for delivery in three months
on the London Metal Exchange extended gains, rising as much as
1.6 percent to $8,364.50 a metric ton, after a European Union
official said euro-area finance ministers reached an agreement
on a second bailout package for  Greece . The metal for May-
delivery on the Comex climbed 2.2 percent to $3.797 a pound.
Aluminum, nickel, zinc, tin and lead gained.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
